Chilean Stocks: Cap, Lan Airlines Fall; Falabella, Ripley Rise

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-28T19:53:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/chilean-stocks-cap-lan-airlines-fall-falabella-ripley-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:14 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.6 percent to 3,901.40. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index retreated 1.3 percent to 2,168.89.  Cap SA (CAP)   fell 1.9 percent to 15,756 pesos, the
biggest loss in a week. Chile’s iron miner and steel producer
declined as base metal prices retreated on concern that
stagnating global growth will reduce demand for raw materials.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   retreated 2.7 percent to 11,774
pesos, its lowest price in six weeks. Latin America’s largest
airline by market value will ask Chile’s antitrust court to
review data used in its evaluation of a proposed takeover of
 Brazil ’s Tam SA, according to a statement e-mailed yesterday.  SACI Falabella (FALAB)   gained 0.6 percent to 4,091.1
pesos, its third day of gains. The retailer, Chile’s largest
publicly traded company, was rated “overweight” at Barclays
Plc by analyst Matthew McClintock.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)   rose 0.7 percent to 420.68
pesos, its second day of gains. Chile’s third-largest department
store operator was assigned an “overweight” rating by
McClintock.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
